This paper is about localization for mobile robots, which is a core problem in robotics. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the use of probability density and filtering techniques, which are common in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and control systems (cs.SY). The paper mentions the use of ultrasound sensors, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) for object detection and localization. Finally, the paper discusses the implementation and testing of the method, which is related to machine learning (cs.LG) for evaluating the performance of the algorithm.
